1
00:00:00,900 --> 00:00:01,867
<i>Someone needs to
be held accountable</i>

2
00:00:01,867 --> 00:00:04,400
<i> for your Grandpa Ben's death.</i>

3
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:06,500
<i> It's Greta's fault.</i>

4
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:08,300
<i> I know a place.</i>

5
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:10,033
<i>It's a property owned
by the Rojas.</i>

6
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:11,667
<i>Ma'am Greta might be
hiding there.</i>

7
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,233
<i> If you know where Greta is,</i>

8
00:00:14,233 --> 00:00:16,333
<i>why don't you just
tell the police?</i>

9
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:18,700
<i> I want to be sure first.</i>

10
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:21,200
<i>Didn't we promise
not to keep secrets anymore?</i>

11
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,667
<i> Ma, I knew it was wrong.</i>

12
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:26,267
I knew what Sir Magnus and Ayen
<i> were doing was wrong.</i>

13
00:00:26,267 --> 00:00:28,033
<i> And I let it happen.</i>

14
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:31,233
<i>That was the reason
Liam got mad at me.</i>

15
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:35,500
<i>After Sir Magnus and Ayen's
relationship ended,</i>

16
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:38,433
<i>I heard Sir Magnus
and Ma'am Greta</i>

17
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:40,500
<i> fighting over that property.</i>

18
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:43,400
<i>I have a feeling
Ma'am Greta's there.</i>

19
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,600
<i> Sir, the patient's awake.</i>

20
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:47,233
He is conscious and responsive.

21
00:00:47,233 --> 00:00:48,567
<i> I suspect that...</i>

22
00:00:48,567 --> 00:00:49,633
<i> He's pretending?</i>

23
00:00:52,233 --> 00:00:53,167
<i> Sir.</i>

24
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:55,767
<i> He's now cleared for transfer.</i>

25
00:00:55,767 --> 00:00:57,767
<i> The rest house by King's Road.</i>

26
00:00:57,767 --> 00:00:59,133
<i>Do you think Mama
could be there?</i>

27
00:00:59,133 --> 00:01:02,167
<i>Well, most probably
since that place is hidden.</i>

28
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:14,367
Greta?

29
00:01:14,367 --> 00:01:15,467
Ma!

30
00:01:15,467 --> 00:01:18,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

31
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:19,633
Ma!

32
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:21,100
Greta.

33
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,300
We know you're here, Greta.

34
00:01:29,167 --> 00:01:30,133
[DOOR CLOSES]

35
00:01:30,567 --> 00:01:31,700
Ma!

36
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:38,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

37
00:01:41,367 --> 00:01:42,433
Ma!

38
00:01:56,667 --> 00:01:57,800
Liam...

39
00:01:57,800 --> 00:02:01,467
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:02:01,467 --> 00:02:02,600
Magnus...

41
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,267
I'm sorry.

42
00:02:16,433 --> 00:02:17,533
I'm sorry.

43
00:02:21,567 --> 00:02:23,233
Forgive me for everything.

44
00:02:28,133 --> 00:02:30,267
I'm the one who should
apologize to you, Greta.

45
00:02:34,667 --> 00:02:36,533
It all started with me.

46
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:38,500
[WHIMPERS]

47
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:42,400
But even if it pains me...

48
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:47,200
you have to surrender
to the police.

49
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:50,467
No.

50
00:02:50,467 --> 00:02:52,500
- [LIAM] Ma.
- I won't turn myself in.

51
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,667
- Ma. Ma...
- Even if you force me,

52
00:02:54,667 --> 00:02:56,200
I won't do it.

53
00:02:57,633 --> 00:02:58,767
Let's go.

54
00:02:59,633 --> 00:03:01,167
[GRETA SOBS]

55
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:08,233
[SOBS, CRIES]

56
00:03:08,233 --> 00:03:15,200
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

57
00:03:23,933 --> 00:03:30,900
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:01,833
[OLSEN] We're here.

59
00:04:06,267 --> 00:04:07,833
I think someone's
already here.

60
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:19,633
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:04:19,633 --> 00:04:21,300
This is Sir Magnus's car.

62
00:04:36,367 --> 00:04:43,300
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

63
00:04:47,467 --> 00:04:48,833
I can't believe

64
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:51,700
that all this time
you were the reason

65
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:53,267
why we had to risk
our lives, Greta.

66
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,733
You?

67
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:56,900
[SOBS SOFTLY]

68
00:04:58,633 --> 00:05:00,667
Try to understand me.

69
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:03,400
I did it

70
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,633
because I wanted
to get all our money back.

71
00:05:06,433 --> 00:05:07,500
Get the money back?

72
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:09,900
All because of that, Ma?

73
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:12,300
Money?

74
00:05:13,767 --> 00:05:14,967
[LIAM] Are you serious?

75
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,933
Did it ever occur to you
that it doesn't matter?

76
00:05:19,067 --> 00:05:21,467
We could've forgiven you

77
00:05:21,467 --> 00:05:23,433
if money were the only problem.

78
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:26,600
How about now?

79
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:29,800
Can you still forgive me?

80
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:35,833
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

81
00:05:35,867 --> 00:05:37,500
Like I've told you before...

82
00:05:38,867 --> 00:05:41,400
whatever happens,
you're still my mother.

83
00:05:45,567 --> 00:05:46,767
But, Ma...

84
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,300
If you truly love us,

85
00:05:52,467 --> 00:05:53,800
you will do what's right.

86
00:05:56,867 --> 00:05:58,767
Please, Greta.
Just come with us.

87
00:05:58,767 --> 00:06:00,967
No, no...

88
00:06:02,367 --> 00:06:04,667
I won't come with you.

89
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:06,433
I can't!

90
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,033
It'll kill me!

91
00:06:09,733 --> 00:06:11,667
I survived 10 years in jail.

92
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,633
You'll live.

93
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:18,433
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

94
00:06:18,433 --> 00:06:19,800
Ma'am Greta, they're right.

95
00:06:22,467 --> 00:06:24,033
What are you doing here?

96
00:06:25,367 --> 00:06:27,133
How did you find this place?

97
00:06:27,133 --> 00:06:30,000
Just turn yourself in, Greta.

98
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,633
I can't. Please...

99
00:06:33,733 --> 00:06:35,667
- "Please"?
- [GRETA SOBBING]

100
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:36,800
- [LOUD SLAP]
- Ah!

101
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:39,133
- That's enough!
- That's for my father!

102
00:06:39,133 --> 00:06:40,667
There's no need
for that, Auntie.

103
00:06:45,467 --> 00:06:47,933
[GRETA CONTINUES SOBBING]

104
00:06:47,933 --> 00:06:49,400
[MAGNUS] Greta...

105
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,967
[GRETA SOBBING LOUDER]

106
00:06:51,967 --> 00:06:58,900
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:07:08,867 --> 00:07:10,367
[LIAM] Ma!

108
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,967
[LIAM] Ma!

109
00:07:19,067 --> 00:07:20,467
- Ma!
- [BANGS ON DOOR]

110
00:07:20,467 --> 00:07:22,000
Ma, open the door!

111
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,967
Are you alright, Ma?

112
00:07:26,967 --> 00:07:28,233
I'm alright, son.

113
00:07:32,867 --> 00:07:34,900
Is that your plan all along?

114
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:36,967
To hide Greta?

115
00:07:36,967 --> 00:07:38,100
No.

116
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:43,100
Whatever happens,
I will surrender Greta.

117
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:44,267
Don't worry.

118
00:07:44,267 --> 00:07:46,433
Just make sure of it, Magnus.

119
00:07:48,433 --> 00:07:51,067
<i> Magnus, I got addicted too.</i>

120
00:07:52,133 --> 00:07:55,300
<i>Addicted? To what?
What do you mean, Greta?</i>

121
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,600
<i> To gambling!</i>

122
00:07:57,467 --> 00:08:01,333
<i> You gambled our money away?</i>

123
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:06,033
<i>Because I wanted to make up
for the money we lost.</i>

124
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,933
<i> Why didn't I know?</i>

125
00:08:11,033 --> 00:08:13,033
<i>Where was I
when all these things</i>

126
00:08:13,033 --> 00:08:14,467
<i> were happening to you?</i>

127
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:17,100
<i>You were busy
with your mistress!</i>

128
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:20,600
<i>- Come here! You flirt!
- Ow! Ow! Ow! Let go!</i>

129
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,933
<i>- I trusted you!
- Wait! Wait, Ma!</i>

130
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:26,467
<i>- Acting like a saint?! Die!
- Ma'am Greta, listen!</i>

131
00:08:26,467 --> 00:08:31,267
<i>We're in love!
Magnus, tell them it's true!</i>

132
00:08:31,267 --> 00:08:33,267
<i> Tell them everything!</i>

133
00:08:33,267 --> 00:08:37,967
<i> Ma'am, he said he loves me
</i>and we're going to be together!

134
00:08:37,967 --> 00:08:40,700
<i>He said he'll leave you
and marry me!</i>

135
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:43,033
- [LOUD SLAPS]
<i> - You witch! Witch!</i>

136
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:49,067
<i>Aside from getting my hopes up
that I can cover our losses,</i>

137
00:08:51,467 --> 00:08:53,433
<i> it somehow helped me forget...</i>

138
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:57,333
that you were enjoying yourself
<i> with someone else.</i>

139
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,500
<i> Wow.</i>

140
00:09:03,233 --> 00:09:05,467
<i> Now, you're blaming me?</i>

141
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:09,733
<i> You dragged me into this mess.</i>

142
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:11,200
<i> Why, Magnus?</i>

143
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:14,400
<i> None of us is clean here!</i>

144
00:09:16,433 --> 00:09:17,633
It's my fault too.

145
00:09:18,633 --> 00:09:20,700
I wasn't a very good husband
to her.

146
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:27,433
Come on, Magnus.
We're all adults here.

147
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:31,600
Greta has no one
to blame but herself.

148
00:09:32,667 --> 00:09:34,767
She has to face the consequences
of her actions.

149
00:09:34,767 --> 00:09:36,367
I got imprisoned!

150
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,467
I paid for a crime
I didn't commit!

151
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,567
She can't escape this.

152
00:09:43,567 --> 00:09:45,167
So many people died.

153
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,567
My father died.

154
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:49,967
She is to blame.

155
00:09:52,467 --> 00:09:54,267
None of this is your fault.

156
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:03,167
You know Greta.
She's not as strong as you.

157
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:08,033
She's vulnerable.

158
00:10:11,133 --> 00:10:13,167
I don't know if
you've heard, but...

159
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,333
she once attempted suicide.

160
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:19,500
Almost losing her
made me realize...

161
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:23,267
that I have to recommit myself
to my family.

162
00:10:24,767 --> 00:10:28,467
Even if the only woman
I ever really loved is...

163
00:10:31,533 --> 00:10:32,667
Ayen?

164
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:39,567
[WISTFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:53,100
Ma'am Greta, please come out!

166
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:57,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

167
00:10:57,633 --> 00:10:58,700
I...

168
00:10:59,433 --> 00:11:02,733
I'm okay! Don't worry!

169
00:11:03,667 --> 00:11:05,367
We're right outside, okay?

170
00:11:06,567 --> 00:11:08,033
Let's give her time.

171
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:18,600
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

172
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:21,700
By the way, how did you
find this rest house?

173
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:27,400
I...

174
00:11:28,533 --> 00:11:30,367
I've been here before.

175
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:35,200
When I drove for
Sir Magnus and...

176
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:38,167
...Ayen.

177
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,533
I'm sorry.

178
00:11:49,267 --> 00:11:50,400
It's okay.

179
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:53,733
- That's all in the past.
- Thanks, but...

180
00:11:56,367 --> 00:11:57,633
I didn't tell you sooner.

181
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:00,467
I admit that was wrong of me.

182
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,267
I shouldn't have hidden it.

183
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,767
I didn't stop Sir Magnus.

184
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:13,700
[WISTFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:25,333
I kept telling myself...

186
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:27,533
that I wasn't in a position
to intervene.

187
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,767
But now...

188
00:12:32,567 --> 00:12:34,333
After everything
that has happened...

189
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:36,533
I...

190
00:12:37,567 --> 00:12:39,400
I can't help but think...

191
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:42,567
that if I had only
done something,

192
00:12:44,767 --> 00:12:46,567
we probably won't be here now.

193
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:48,800
But you're right.

194
00:12:50,533 --> 00:12:51,933
I was just a kid.

195
00:12:53,567 --> 00:12:55,933
I was just a fatherless kid.

196
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:03,933
Maybe that's why I was craving
your father's acceptance.

197
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,667
[YOUNG LIAM]
<i> Isn't he Aunt Wendy's son?</i>

198
00:13:08,667 --> 00:13:10,000
<i> I finally have a playmate!</i>

199
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,333
<i> By the way, I'm Liam.</i>

200
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:13,767
[YOUNG OLSEN]
<i> I'm Olsen.</i>

201
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:20,700
[WISTFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

202
00:13:31,067 --> 00:13:33,333
<i> Would you like to play?</i>

203
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:35,500
<i> Papa gave this to me.</i>

204
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:37,033
<i> I envy you.</i>

205
00:13:37,767 --> 00:13:39,600
<i> Your papa is kind.</i>

206
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:44,700
<i>You're lucky you have a father
who gives you presents.</i>

207
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:47,633
<i> My papa has left.</i>

208
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:53,367
<i> Why? Where is your father?</i>

209
00:13:53,967 --> 00:13:57,933
<i>He's dead.
I didn't even get to meet him.</i>

210
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:01,767
<i> Would you like us to share?</i>

211
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:03,800
<i> Share?</i>

212
00:14:04,767 --> 00:14:06,467
<i> Your father?</i>

213
00:14:06,467 --> 00:14:07,900
<i> No!</i>

214
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:09,900
<i> I meant this PSP.</i>

215
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:11,600
<i> You serious?</i>

216
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:12,933
<i> Here.</i>

217
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:16,467
I did everything you asked for.

218
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:19,733
I took up Computer Engineering.

219
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:21,800
<i> I finished it.</i>

220
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:24,300
<i> I graduated summa cum laude.</i>

221
00:14:25,067 --> 00:14:27,667
<i>You can't say I neglected
my studies.</i>

222
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:31,000
<i> Yes, you would follow me,</i>

223
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:33,333
<i> but with conditions.</i>

224
00:14:34,367 --> 00:14:35,700
<i> You would do it,</i>

225
00:14:37,667 --> 00:14:40,600
<i> but you'd still go against me.</i>

226
00:14:42,733 --> 00:14:47,067
<i>If you think you can stand
on your own two feet now,</i>

227
00:14:49,433 --> 00:14:51,967
<i>you're free to go.
Leave. Goodbye. Adios.</i>

228
00:14:53,667 --> 00:14:55,633
<i> Don't bother coming back.</i>

229
00:14:57,667 --> 00:15:00,500
<i>I won't gain anything
from you anyway, right?</i>

230
00:15:02,033 --> 00:15:05,567
<i>And you won't gain
anything from me.</i>

231
00:15:11,433 --> 00:15:13,767
<i>I didn't come here
to fight with you.</i>

232
00:15:13,767 --> 00:15:16,400
[LAUGHS SCORNFULLY]

233
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:19,700
<i>Someone just told me
to say goodbye to you</i>

234
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:23,833
<i>because you are still
my father.</i>

235
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:28,100
<i>- So, I'm here to do that.
- All right.</i>

236
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:32,933
<i> Goodbye, Pa.</i>

237
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:39,100
- [OLSEN]<i> Is this a bad time?
</i>- [MAGNUS] It's fine. Come in.

238
00:15:40,467 --> 00:15:43,033
<i>I'll be transferring you
to the marketing team.</i>

239
00:15:43,033 --> 00:15:45,633
<i>They're a great team.
You'll learn a lot from them.</i>

240
00:15:45,633 --> 00:15:48,100
I want to be part of your team.

241
00:15:49,167 --> 00:15:50,867
[MAGNUS]
<i> I'll train you myself.</i>

242
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:56,633
I know.

243
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:05,933
Good thing Doc Ivan
examined him.

244
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:08,867
His pupillary light
reflex is intact.

245
00:16:08,900 --> 00:16:12,733
And, uh, deep tendon reflexes
are present.

246
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:15,833
His breathing pattern
is also voluntary.

247
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:18,733
Every sign indicates that
the patient is conscious.

248
00:16:18,733 --> 00:16:25,667
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

249
00:16:28,567 --> 00:16:29,767
Emil Padua.

250
00:16:30,667 --> 00:16:32,000
Drop the act.

251
00:16:32,733 --> 00:16:34,833
Unless you want another case
filed against you.

252
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:43,667
[SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:46,533
That doctor of yours is good.

254
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:50,100
He's young, but he's good.

255
00:16:51,167 --> 00:16:53,067
He'll go places.

256
00:16:53,933 --> 00:16:56,600
[TENSE STING]

257
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,900
[HUFFS]

258
00:16:57,900 --> 00:16:59,700
Where are your accomplices?

259
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:06,767
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

260
00:17:09,867 --> 00:17:11,767
We'll transfer you
to our facility.

261
00:17:13,667 --> 00:17:15,100
We'll talk there.

262
00:17:15,133 --> 00:17:20,800
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

263
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:30,533
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:17:30,533 --> 00:17:37,100
[GRETA SOBBING]

265
00:17:38,133 --> 00:17:39,400
<i> What happened?</i>

266
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:48,367
<i> I just defended myself.</i>

267
00:17:58,367 --> 00:18:05,300
[WHIMPERING]

268
00:18:08,233 --> 00:18:11,700
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

269
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:17,567
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

270
00:18:17,567 --> 00:18:20,033
[BREATH SHAKES]

271
00:18:32,233 --> 00:18:35,467
<i>Emil Padua's being transferred
to a police facility today.</i>

272
00:18:35,467 --> 00:18:38,100
<i>I hope they find
the rest of his accomplices.</i>

273
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:39,333
<i> Even Greta Roja?</i>

274
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:41,767
<i>I really didn't expect
she'd do that.</i>

275
00:18:41,767 --> 00:18:45,400
<i>I've always felt like
I'm competing with you.</i>

276
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:48,667
<i>Magnus and I had an affair
while you were married.</i>

277
00:18:48,667 --> 00:18:50,267
<i> But I walked away.</i>

278
00:18:50,267 --> 00:18:53,533
<i>You did. But you remained
in my husband's heart.</i>

279
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:56,400
<i> Can we not turn Mama in yet?</i>

280
00:18:56,433 --> 00:18:58,267
<i>- We've talked about this.
- I know.</i>

281
00:18:58,267 --> 00:18:59,600
<i>She's going to face
a serious case.</i>

282
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:03,400
Your mother made a terrible lie.
<i> A lot of people died, Liam.</i>

283
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:06,033
<i>But can you let me
be with her for a while?</i>

284
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,067
<i>How have you been?
You're still alive?</i>

285
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:14,067
<i>We both survived.
Lucky us, huh?</i>

286
00:19:14,067 --> 00:19:16,333
<i>General Cabral and I
had an agreement.</i>

287
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:18,100
<i>He said he'll give me
protection.</i>

288
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:20,367
<i>Why are you putting me in jail
with this animal?</i>

289
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:23,067
<i>Animal? You're all
the same, Jacinto.</i>

290
00:19:23,667 --> 00:19:26,333
<i>Let's see if you
can escape this.</i>

291
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:40,100
[TIRES SCREECHING]

292
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:42,100
<i>- It's an ambush!
- [BRAKES SQUEAL]</i>

293
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:48,833
[SMOKE GRENADE HISSING]

294
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:54,433
[ECHOING GUNSHOT]

295
00:19:54,433 --> 00:19:57,700
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

296
00:19:57,700 --> 00:20:04,600
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
